timelineItems.text: A little bit of the old Tchani in that turnover. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC

timelineItems.desc: Two Eastern Conference powerhouses collide at RFK Stadium with a playoff berth on the line.
timelineItems.title: KICKOFF: D.C. United vs Columbus Crew SC

timelineItems.name: John Bava III
timelineItems.text: Columbus will be missing Waylon Francis at left back who's still getting over a quad strain. #CrewSC #DCvCLB

timelineItems.text: Interesting formation shift according to DC broadcast - #CrewSC alleged to use 4-5-1 with Higuain in between Tchani and Trapp.

timelineItems.text: That's a big road win for the #CrewSC right there!!

timelineItems.text: Beating #DCU is the best. THE BEST. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Patrick Guldan
timelineItems.text: DCU trying to pressure initially, but #CrewSC able to pass around it so far.

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 21‘: Kamara clears a United corner and #CrewSC gains possession. #DCvCLB

timelineItems.name: Massive Report
timelineItems.text: 20’ 0-0. Both teams have had chances, but neither #CrewSC or #DCU able to break through.

timelineItems.name: Chris
timelineItems.text: Both GK's came to play tonight. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: CSN D.C. United
timelineItems.text: Kitchen tries from outside the box, but he couldn't get a lot on the shot. Still scoreless in the 23rd minute. #DCUTalk

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: 24' #CrewSC with a free kick from a dangerous spot, but Higuain's service doesn't get past the first defender.

timelineItems.name: Sean Maslin
timelineItems.text: Saborio with an innocent little flick...Is he finally getting his scoring touch back #dcu #dcutalk #DCvCLB

timelineItems.desc: Goal!  D.C. United 0, Columbus Crew SC 1. Ethan Finlay (Columbus Crew SC) right footed shot from the left side of the six yard box to the top left corner.
timelineItems.title: GOAL: Ethan Finlay turns, shoots and scores from inside the 6-yard box

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 25‘: Meram connects with Kamara in the box! He sends one in from the left channel and Kei gets his head on it but it's high. #CrewSC #DCvCLB

timelineItems.name: Sebastian Salazar
timelineItems.text: 25 minutes in, we're seeing real goalie display here at #DCU vs #CrewSC. Bill Hamid and Steve Clark proving why they're two of #MLS best.

timelineItems.name: Tylor Arthurs
timelineItems.text: ETHAAAAAAAAAANNNNN!!!!!! #CREWSC @EthanFinlay13

timelineItems.name: Todd Fichtenberg
timelineItems.text: My least fave to my most fave! #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Crewbacca
timelineItems.text: Tyson Wahl for President #Crewsc #🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥

timelineItems.name: Football & Football
timelineItems.text: WELL HELLO MR. FINLEY #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Samurai Hitman
timelineItems.text: An insanely great goal from Finlay. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Rob Mixer
timelineItems.text: The Wahl-Finlay combo was quite surprising but also quite awesome #CrewSC

timelineItems.desc: Tony Tchani (Columbus Crew SC) hits the bar with a right footed shot from the center of the box.
timelineItems.title: CROSSBAR: Tony Tchani's well-times volley is denied by the crossbar

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 3‘: Meram gets the first look for #CrewSC, but his shot is blocked and it's a corner for Columbus. #DCvCLB

timelineItems.name: Andrew King
timelineItems.text: Hard to overstate how much it alters the game for #CrewSC to score first. If DC gets the first goal, this thing grinds to a halt.

timelineItems.name: CSN D.C. United
timelineItems.text: Saborio goes on a great run to get behind the defense, but he just can't put it home. In the 31st min, DCU trails 1-0 #DCUTalk

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: FWIW, #DCU has the best record in MLS when allowing the first goal (7-8-2). Wonder if that means much given recent run of play. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Massive Report
timelineItems.text: 30’ #CrewSC looking much sharper since the goal, but Saborio gets off a dangerous shot on the counter.

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: With that finish, @EthanFinlay13 becomes just the seventh player in #CrewSC history to register 20 career goals & 20 career assists. #DCvCLB

timelineItems.name: Matt Bernhardt
timelineItems.text: Through 30 minutes, #CrewSC leads possession battle about 60/40

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: 33' Tony Tchani with a nice feed to Justin Meram. He buries it, but is ruled offside. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 33': Justin Meram with a great shot from Tchani's slot, but he's offside. No goal. #CrewSC #DCvCLB

timelineItems.name: Darbs
timelineItems.text: Why are we afraid to go to Afful when he's wide open? #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Carl Lettow
timelineItems.text: Alex's 30-something birthday, spending it with @dcunited ! #VAMOSUNITED http://t.co/h5JNzgchLa

timelineItems.name: Massive Scoop
timelineItems.text: United pressing is working well. #CrewSC having trouble switching flanks.

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: 3' Federico Higuain taking the #CrewSC corner. Must be back to full health...and Tchani nearly scores. Rings the post.

timelineItems.name: Andrew Chwalik
timelineItems.text: Supporting the @ColumbusCrewSC all the way out here in Washington, DC! #CrewSC #WhereIsTheYellow http://t.co/NGzLMhKQFd

timelineItems.text: 40’ #CrewSC finding space on the right side in the past few minutes. Afful getting forward.

timelineItems.name: Frankie Hejduk
timelineItems.text: Goaaaaal!! Oh yeah!! Crewzin' w/ the boys!! #CCSA #CrewSC #1-0 #party #letsgo http://t.co/KX3BxpHEqf

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 41‘: Pipa finds Kamara on a long bouncing ball into the box! Hamid reads it and he's there for the save. #CrewSC #DCvCLB

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: Boswell with a little contact on Kamara while waiting for a throw-in. Kamara gestures to DC bench: bring it on. #CrewSC #DCvCLB

timelineItems.name: Todd Fichtenberg
timelineItems.text: That was a sweet fake out to escort the ball out for a goal kick. #CrewSC

timelineItems.desc: Goal!  D.C. United 0, Columbus Crew SC 2. Kei Kamara (Columbus Crew SC) right footed shot from the center of the box to the bottom right corner.
timelineItems.title: GOAL: Kei Kamara turns on the jets and doubles the Crew lead

timelineItems.name: Lincoln Kickbush
timelineItems.text: Vamos United!!! DC United can clinch a playoff spot. #DCvCLB #VAMOSUNITED http://t.co/LojCef4x3N

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: Warmups are in full swing. #CrewSC #DCvCLB http://t.co/AeWeTlXC1b

timelineItems.desc: Steve Birnbaum (D.C. United) is shown the yellow card for a bad foul.
timelineItems.title: YELLOW CARD: Steve Birnbaum is booked for a rough challenge

timelineItems.name: MassiveCity
timelineItems.text: Tyson Wahl's been the best defender for the #CrewSC tonight. Recognize. #ALLOFTHEWAHL #DCvCLB

timelineItems.name: KC Williamson
timelineItems.text: You a bad man @keikamara #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: What a through ball from Tony Tchani. That pass went half the field and got to Kamara in stride, who burned Birnbaum. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Mike Miller
timelineItems.text: How slow is that defender Kamara just beat? That pass from Tchani took 12 seconds to get there, defender still couldn't catch up. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Pablo Maurer
timelineItems.text: Boy, Tony Tchani is having a hell of a game tonight for the Crew. #CrewSC #DCU #MLS

timelineItems.name: Samurai Hitman
timelineItems.text: #HeartShapedHands #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Matt Bernhardt
timelineItems.text: So no Francis or Sauro in the gameday roster for #CrewSC. Most everything else looks like a first choice selection.

timelineItems.name: Andrew King
timelineItems.text: The key to this game for #CrewSC will be patience. DC will not break easily, and Columbus can't get frustrated and start being irresponsible

timelineItems.name: Daniel Karell
timelineItems.text: Very impressive spell of possession for #CrewSC there. Almost forgot this game was in DC.

timelineItems.desc: Attempt saved. Justin Meram (Columbus Crew SC) left footed shot from the left side of the box is saved in the bottom left corner.
timelineItems.title: SAVE: Bill Hamid punches away a rocket from Meram

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 5‘: Tony Tchani with another shot! He hits it from about 35 yards out and Hamid tips it wide. #CrewSC #DCvCLB

timelineItems.name: Anthony Precourt
timelineItems.text: Tchani is bringing it #crewsc

timelineItems.name: CSN D.C. United
timelineItems.text: Chris Rolfe serves a beautiful ball in the box and connects with Alvaro Saborio's head but the ball goes just wide. #DCUTalk

timelineItems.desc: Perry Kitchen (D.C. United) is shown the yellow card.
timelineItems.title: YELLOW CARD: Perry Kitchen is booked for rough play

timelineItems.name: Darbs
timelineItems.text: Kei now looking to boost that assist total. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Amy Bernhardt
timelineItems.text: How does Hamid not have a hole in his chest after that shot by Meram? #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: CSN D.C. United
timelineItems.text: Bill Hamid makes a great save giving Columbus their 5th corner for the night. #DCUTalk

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: Here's the question: Can #CrewSC find that third goal to remove all doubt? Couldn't do it last weekend, and 2-1 final was nervy at end.

timelineItems.name: Darbs
timelineItems.text: Hamid got that by the skin of his teeth. Finlay could had a second. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 64‘: Pipa finds Finlay through, but he turns and Hamid is at the top of the box to greet him and clear it. #CrewSC #DCvCLB

timelineItems.desc: Penalty conceded by Chris Klute (Columbus Crew SC) with a hand ball in the penalty area.
timelineItems.title: HANDBALL: Chris Klute's handball in the box results in a penalty kick for D.C.

timelineItems.name: Massive Report
timelineItems.text: #CrewSC totally dominating the past several minutes. DC looking spent.

timelineItems.desc: Goal!  D.C. United 1, Columbus Crew SC 2. Chris Rolfe (D.C. United) converts the penalty with a right footed shot to the top left corner.
timelineItems.title: PK GOAL: Chris Rolfe rifles it past Steve Clark to get United back in the game

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 67‘: A penalty kick is called as Chris Klute is called for a hand ball in the box. #CrewSC #DCvCLB

timelineItems.name: Amy Bernhardt
timelineItems.text: Yeah. That's going to get called as a handball almost every time. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: 68' Steve Clark gets a hand on it, but Chris Rolfe converts the PK. It's 2-1 #CrewSC now.

timelineItems.name: Pablo Maurer
timelineItems.text: Rolfe lines up over the PK (guess Fabi's done taking them for now) and fires a bullet into the upper 90. 2-1 #CrewSC. Life left in this one?

timelineItems.name: CSN D.C. United
timelineItems.text: Hamid is earning his pay early on in this one! Another great opportunity for Columbus is met with an even better save. #DCUTalk

timelineItems.desc: Chris Klute (Columbus Crew SC) is shown the yellow card for a bad foul.
timelineItems.title: YELLOW CARD: Chris Klute is booked for an off-the-ball foul

timelineItems.name: Pablo Maurer
timelineItems.text: Sean Franklin has been a bright spot for #DCU. Would like to see him overlap even more, tough ask tho against these wingers. #MLS #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Matt Bernhardt
timelineItems.text: Could Klute's yellow be because he played the ball from the ground before he went off injured? #DCvCLB #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: 76' Hector Jimenez comes in for Chris Klute. Things unraveled rather quickly for Klute, who filled in 4 Waylon Francis at left back. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Massive Scoop
timelineItems.text: I have no problem with Tchani trying from outside the box. Make United come out. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Sal Cipriano
timelineItems.text: Wow, @dcunited lucky to have the best goalie in the league tonight! #Crew96 feeling it.

timelineItems.name: Dave Edinger
timelineItems.text: BRB gotta go buy a Tchani jersey. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: CSN D.C. United
timelineItems.text: #DCU puts another goal away but referee calls it offsides. #DCUTalk

timelineItems.name: Matt Bernhardt
timelineItems.text: This would be a good game for Steindorsson to finally get his name on a #CrewSC scoresheet...

timelineItems.name: Andrew King
timelineItems.text: I planned on asking Gregg Berhalter if this was the most complete #CrewSC performance of the season...and then the last 15 minutes happened.

timelineItems.name: Ralph Schudel
timelineItems.text: POGATETZ!!! #CrewSC #FeedtheDog

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: Parkhurst shifting out to right back. Pogatetz and Wahl in the center, Jimenez on the left. Afful pushing forward on the right. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Andrew King
timelineItems.text: #CrewSC doing their best to give this thing away. Saborio was absolutely onside.

timelineItems.name: Helloyd Kromlinson
timelineItems.text: Tyson Wahl has come up pretty big in this match. Props to him. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Daniel Karell
timelineItems.text: Replay shows that was a good goal for Saborio that was ruled out. Should be 2-2. #dcunited #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 88‘: Steve Clark comes out to snag a cross into the box from Kitchen. #CrewSC #DCvCLB

timelineItems.name: Adam Jardy
timelineItems.text: 92' Kristinn Steindorsson putitng forth all kinds of effort right now. Running at every ball on either side or end of the field. #CrewSC

timelineItems.name: MassiveCity
timelineItems.text: #CrewSC are about to be the leaders in the Supporters Shield race. This is MLS.

timelineItems.name: Columbus Crew SC
timelineItems.text: 90‘+2': Afful dribbles up the right channel and is fouled. Taylor Kemp is issued a yellow card. #CrewSC #DCvCLB
